result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Rebecca R.M. Debroux in court with attorney Jessica L Schuster.  Galen Bayne-Allison appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Cases called 16CM26 and 15CM262  Called  3:41 pm  Plea agreement 15CM262 plea to ct.  Fine 100 plus cost.  expungement.  16CM26 plea to ct 2 expungement.  Court indicates both cases will not be expunged.  State will dismiss and read in 15CM262.  Court explains that expungement still may not be granted.  State moves to dismiss and read in 15CM262.  Court will dismiss & read in 15CM262.  Plea questionnaire filed and reviewed .  16CM26 Ct 2 - No contest plea.  Ct 1 dismissed.  Constitutional rights and right to jury trial reviewed.  Elements and penalties reviewed.  Warrant vacated in this case.  Court finds def understands charge, penalties and rights.  Stipulate to facts in complaint.  Court finds factual basis.  Plea accepted, found guilty of Bail Jumping.  State presents sentencing arguments.    Atty Schuster presents sentencing arguments.  Nothing by def  Court orders  withheld sentence  1 year probation, AODA assessment & follow through, costs DNA Sample & 200 Surcharge, Credit for 2 days if revoked.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Court gives reason if going to order expungement. Court not granting expungement. Sentence on 16CM26.
